.TH holberton-shell 1 "August 2023" "Holberton Simple Shell Project"
.SH NAME
holberton-shell \- Holberton Simple Shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
holberton-shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
The holberton-shell is a basic Unix command-line interpreter developed as a project for Holberton School. It allows users to execute commands, manage processes, and navigate the file system.

.SH OPTIONS
The holberton-shell supports the following options:

.PP
.B \-h, \--help
Displays a help message and exits.

.SH COMMANDS
The holberton-shell supports the execution of standard Unix commands and provides the following built-in commands:

.PP
.B exit
Exit the shell.

.PP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.

.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
Run the holberton-shell in interactive mode by executing the compiled binary. The shell will display a prompt, wait for user input, and execute commands accordingly.

.PP
$ ./holberton-shell
($) /bin/ls
file1.txt  file2.txt  directory/
($)
($) exit
$

.SH NON-INTERACTIVE MODE
Commands can also be executed in non-interactive mode by piping input to the shell.

.PP
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./holberton-shell
file1.txt  file2.txt  directory/
$

.SH EXIT STATUS
The holberton-shell returns the following exit statuses:

.PP
0: Successful execution.
1: General error.
2: Invalid command.

.SH AUTHOR
The holberton-shell was developed by Khaled Jallouli (jallouli.khaled.2001@gmail.com) as a project for Holberton School.

